# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Knot Desktop — local development environment template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Setup:
#   1. Copy to apps/desktop/.env (desktop can also read apps/web/.env)
#   2. Use the SAME Clerk publishable key as apps/web
#   3. Point KNOT_WEB_APP_URL at the running Next.js app
#   4. Run web first (`pnpm --filter web dev`), then `pnpm --filter desktop dev`
#
# Packaging / production: see example.env.production and README § Packaging.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Clerk (same Application as web) ──────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...

NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_FALLBACK_REDIRECT_URL=/dashboard
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_FALLBACK_REDIRECT_URL=/dashboard

# ── Next.js web app (API + dashboard + share links) ──────────────────────────
# Desktop uploads chunks here; the API writes to B2.
KNOT_WEB_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Optional Vite aliases (usually unnecessary if NEXT_PUBLIC_* / KNOT_* are set)
# VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# VITE_KNOT_API_URL=

# Optional: override Frontend API host if auto-derived host is wrong
# (Clerk Dashboard → API keys → Frontend API URL host, e.g. fitting-trout-62.clerk.accounts.dev)
# VITE_CLERK_FAPI_HOST=

# ── Desktop Clerk / OAuth (required for Google & GitHub) ─────────────────────
# In Clerk Dashboard:
# 1. Native applications → enable Native API
# 2. Allowed redirect URL (exact, with trailing slash):
#      knot://app/
# 3. Social connections → enable Google and GitHub (same as web)
#
# The desktop UI loads over knot://app (not http://localhost). That is required
# by @clerk/electron so Clerk does not reject requests with
# "Origin and Authorization headers conflict" (HTTP 400).
#
# Recording: each session writes independently playable chunk-NNNN.webm files
# (~5s). While signed in, chunks upload via the Next.js API and a /watch share
# link appears after the cloud session starts (watchable once chunk 0 lands).
# Offline mode stays local-only.
#
# If Cisco Umbrella (or similar) blocks B2 on the API host, point
# KNOT_WEB_APP_URL at a cloud-hosted Knot web deploy instead.
